- The cities mentioned, San Francisco and Los Angeles, are major metropolitan areas in California, known for their high cost of living; 
- A property type refers to the classification of a property, such as single-family homes, apartments, or condominiums;
- Median house value and median rent are measures of central tendency that indicate the midpoint of house values and rents in an area, where half the values are higher and half are lower;
- Data validation is the process of checking the quality and accuracy of data, ensuring that it meets certain criteria or standards; 
- The figure of $500,000 is used as a threshold for the average median house value, suggesting a focus on higher-end properties.
